{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, integrated sensing and communication (ISAC) is emerging as a promising technique to increase spectral efficiency [12].",
    "In addition, compared with the traditional separate setups, ISAC not only reduces the mutual interference, but also enables mutual benefits to the two systems [13].",
    "In particular, the sensing capability helps to improve the communication performance [14][15][16] and vice versa [17][18][19].",
    "For example, the sensing functionality can enhance the physical layer security (PLS) by estimating the direction of a potential eavesdropper [14], and the information exchange among multiple sensing nodes enables a cooperative sensing performance gain [19].",
    "Leveraging the above advantages, ISAC is considered a key enabler for 5G in various domains such as smart home [20], smart manufacturing [21], vehicle to everything (V2X) [22,23], and Internet of Things (IoT) [24], as shown in Figure 1."
  ]
}